The General Assembly is the main deliberative body of the UN. It is composed of representatives of all member states, and it meets in regular annual sessions. How cobalt-60 is produced Cobalt-60 is produced in a nuclear reactor. When the reactor is operating, the fuel rods are bombarded by neutrons. These neutrons cause the atoms of the fuel rods to split, producing more neutrons and more fission. The neutrons that are produced are absorbed by other atoms, which then split and produce more neutrons. This process is called a chain reaction.
